fehd.ADR_TC: 香港中環德己立街21號2樓,3樓,4樓及5樓

result.adr_address: 21 D'Aguilar St, Central, Hong Kong
result.name: Cafe Siam

reviews.text:
Terrible experience. They served my dish with pork in it when I specifically ordered a vegetarian dish. The waiter simply shrugged it off and said 'sorry' when I pointed it out. Service was less than halfhearted - waiters were walking around but were extremely inattentive. We almost had to yell for their attention.
The food was good but the experience was so unpleasant that I would never come back again.
Fast take away. Cheap and affordable good thai

Lunch deal was good value for a place in Central HK. Good quality food, but not very authentic - depends on what you get! Spring rolls were good as was the clear soup with pork. Green curry is recommended, but fried rice tasted a bit like the food on airplanes. What made it not such a great experience was the dessert (coconut jelly) and the music choice (annoying pop and loud). Waitress was kind enough to reduce the volume.
Nice view, delicious food is worth it.
Ordered takeaway & straightforward conclusion right away is “lousy & disappointing”. Definitely no 2nd attempt! The Pad Thai & fried rice were tasted like rubber!

result.adr_address: 香港中環德己立街21號
result.name: Cafe Siam

reviews.text:
Thai for sure@Cafe Siam 

地址: 中環德己立街21號The Plaza 2-3樓

Thai Thai Thai ，東南亞菜系內，泰國菜是我首選，多選擇烹煮變化方法也多，不容易吃悶。

燈光比較暗黑，有情調但影相唔好睇

 椰汁青咖哩，可加肉 豬雞牛其中一個肉。青咖哩比較香而不辣，因加入了椰奶，我直頭當湯飲架！不能吃飯的我，都有衝動點一碗。料有泰式茄子及些蔬菜，豐富開胃令人食指大動。

鱸魚一條原條上，焗的好香因中間塞了香料，增強香氣又去腥。

蒜香辣椒絲炒雜菜, my staple dish , 蒜蓉炒無咁重味同鹹，亦都是很習慣的口味。

Signature salad ,有豆腐同花生醬做salad dressing ,甜甜地幾似食satay 個醬的。

泰菜香料多，而又不會像中菜下味精，靠不同spice 吸引人。

Service was less than halfhearted - waiters were walking around but were extremely inattentive. We almost had to yell for their attention.
The food was good but the experience was so unpleasant that I would never come back again.
Fast take away. Cheap and affordable good thai

Lunch deal was good value for a place in Central HK. Good quality food, but not very authentic - depends on what you get! Spring rolls were good as was the clear soup with pork. Green curry is recommended, but fried rice tasted a bit like the food on airplanes. What made it not such a great experience was the dessert (coconut jelly) and the music choice (annoying pop and loud). Waitress was kind enough to reduce the volume.
Nice view, delicious food is worth it.
